\\"Terms\\\") constitute a legally binding agreement between GRClass (\\\"Company\\\", \\\"We\\\", \\\"Us\\\", or \\\"Our\\\") and the user (\\\"User\\\", \\\"You\\\"). These Terms govern your access to and use of the GRClass platform (\\\"Platform\\\", \\\"Service\\\"), including all associated management tools, reporting systems, and certification modules.</p><p>By accessing or using the Platform, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, you must cease use of the Platform immediately.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>2. Scope of Service</strong></h3><p>GRClass provides a comprehensive digital infrastructure for the maritime industry, specifically focusing on:</p><p>Certification Lifecycle: Requesting, managing, and issuing vessel certifications.</p><p>Survey Management: Scheduling and tracking survey jobs and inspection reporting.</p><p>Compliance Tracking: Monitoring regulatory requirements and certificate validity.</p><p>Financial Operations: Tracking invoices and payment status related to technical services.</p><p>Note: GRClass acts as a digital facilitator. We do not physically perform inspections unless a specific, separate service contract is executed.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>3. User Roles and Access Control</strong></h3><p>The Platform utilizes Role-Based Access Control (RBAC). Users are categorized into roles including, but not limited to:</p><p>Client: Ship Owners and Managers.</p><p>Surveyor: Field personnel providing inspection data.</p><p>Technical Staff: Technical Officers (TO), Technical Managers (TM), and General Managers (GM).</p><p>Administrator: System-level management.</p><p>Users must strictly adhere to the permissions granted to their specific role. Any attempt to bypass security protocols or access unauthorized data will result in immediate account termination.</p><h3><br></h3><h3><strong>4. Account Responsibility and Security</strong></h3><p>Confidentiality: You are responsible for safeguarding your login credentials. Any activity occurring under your account is your sole responsibility.</p><p>Data Integrity: You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during the registration and usage process.</p><p>Unauthorized Use: You must notify GRClass immediately of any breach of security or unauthorized use of your account.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>5. Job Requests and Survey Protocols</strong></h3><p>Submission: Clients may submit requests for vessel surveys through the dashboard.</p><p>Discretion: GRClass reserves the right to approve or reject requests, assign specific surveyors, and request additional documentation at its discretion.</p><p>Surveyor Conduct: Surveyors are mandated to submit truthful, evidence-backed inspection data.</p><p>Verification: GRClass may require \\\"re-work\\\" or additional evidence if submitted reports do not meet the Company’s technical standards.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>6. Certification Issuance and Validity</strong></h3><p>Certificates are issued digitally based on successful technical reviews, compliance verification, and payment confirmation.</p><p>Revocation Rights: GRClass reserves the right to suspend, modify, or revoke any certificate if subsequent non-compliance or fraudulent data is discovered.</p><p>Limited Scope: Certificates are valid only within the specific scope and duration explicitly stated on the document.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>7. Financial Terms</strong></h3><p>Fees: Users agree to pay all applicable fees for surveys, certification, and documentation as per the current fee schedule.</p><p>Payment Prerequisite: Unless otherwise agreed in writing, certificates will be held in \\\"Pending\\\" status until full payment of the relevant invoice is confirmed.</p><p>Late Payments: GRClass reserves the right to suspend platform access for accounts with overdue invoices.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>8. Data Accuracy and Audit</strong></h3><p>User Liability: The accuracy of vessel details and uploaded documentation remains the responsibility of the User.</p><p>Audit Logs: For compliance and security, all actions performed on the platform are logged. By using the system, you consent to the monitoring and auditing of your activity for regulatory purposes.</p><h3><br></h3><h3><strong>9. Platform Availability and Maintenance</strong></h3><p>While GRClass strives for 99.9% uptime, we do not guarantee:</p><p>Uninterrupted access during emergency maintenance.</p><p>Real-time processing speeds during peak server loads.</p><p>Immediate issuance of certificates following a survey (subject to technical review).</p><h3><br></h3><h3><strong>10. Limitation of Liability</strong></h3><p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, GRClass shall not be liable for:</p><p>Operational losses or vessel downtime.</p><p>Delays caused by regulatory bodies or third-party surveyors.</p><p>Fines or penalties imposed by Port State Control or Flag States.</p><p>Indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from platform use.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>11. Intellectual Property</strong></h3><p>All system architecture, UI/UX design, report templates, and proprietary algorithms remain the exclusive Intellectual Property of GRClass. No part of the platform may be replicated, reverse-engineered, or distributed without prior written consent.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>12. Confidentiality</strong></h3><p>All data processed through the platform is considered sensitive. GRClass maintains industry-standard encryption. Users are prohibited from sharing internal technical reports or system screenshots with third parties without authorization.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>13. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</strong></h3><p>These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Insert Country/State]. Any disputes arising under these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in [Insert City/Jurisdiction].</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>14. Contact Information</strong></h3><p>For legal inquiries or technical support, please contact:</p><p>GRClass Support Team Email: support@grclass.com</p><p>Address: [Insert Full Company Address]</p><p>Website: www.grclass.com</p><p>Acknowledgement: By continuing to use the GRClass Platform, you acknowledge that you have read and agreed to these Terms and Conditions.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>\", \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-04T10:18:27.000Z\", \"faq_items\": null, \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-07T03:37:45.000Z\", \"updated_by\": \"019c79a4-3eee-731a-9eff-b0eed303e215\", \"content_type\": \"PAGE\", \"is_published\": true, \"published_at\": \"2026-04-04T00:00:00.000Z\", \"thumbnail_url\": \"\"}','{\"id\": \"d4371572-6d45-41ec-8657-33b9ad401415\", \"slug\": \"terms-and-condition\", \"title\": \"Terms and condition\", \"body_html\": \"<h1><strong>Terms and Conditions</strong></h1><p>GRClass Platform Last Updated: April 07, 2026</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>1. Introduction and Acceptance</strong></h3><p>These Terms and Conditions (\\\"Terms\\\") constitute a legally binding agreement between GRClass (\\\"Company\\\", \\\"We\\\", \\\"Us\\\", or \\\"Our\\\") and the user (\\\"User\\\", \\\"You\\\"). These Terms govern your access to and use of the GRClass platform (\\\"Platform\\\", \\\"Service\\\"), including all associated management tools, reporting systems, and certification modules.</p><p>By accessing or using the Platform, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, you must cease use of the Platform immediately.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>2. Scope of Service</strong></h3><p>GRClass provides a comprehensive digital infrastructure for the maritime industry, specifically focusing on:</p><p>Certification Lifecycle: Requesting, managing, and issuing vessel certifications.</p><p>Survey Management: Scheduling and tracking survey jobs and inspection reporting.</p><p>Compliance Tracking: Monitoring regulatory requirements and 